screen_name: After 47 long days, I am officially recovered from Covid-19! I start back to work tomorrow!!! Thank you to everyone for your care and concern. Thank you for all the prayers and positive messages. The virus is still out there so take care of yourself and each other 💜
I’m off for Covid test #4 today. I think I’m starting to revert to being a child because after every test I’m like “what else can I shove up my nose?” 🤣🤣🤣jk

I got my results of my second test. I tested positive. The first negative was a false negative. That’s why they wanted me to take two tests. I go back next Thursday to get tested again, which will be a month since my original test. 🤦‍♀️😞

So Covid-19 is still kicking our ass. My wife tested positive which we kinda knew she would. We’ve all lost our sense of taste and smell, that sucks. Every day is a battle but we battle it together. Hopefully we will be over this bs soon.

I got my test results back. I tested positive for Covid-19. I’m feeling better today than I have all week but I still feel weak. People, stay home. Don’t go to the store just because you’re bored. Essential workers can catch it too. 😢

Most of you may know that me and my family are still trying to recover from Covid. Please tell me why my brother in law’s fiancé just sent us a text tell us what we can get them for Christmas. Not “hey how are y’all feeling” or “how’s it going”. Just a pic of what they want. 🤦‍♀️🖕

We still have some issues catching our breath sometimes and our taste and smell are slowly coming back. Now my friends from work are out with it. I feel like it’ll be a never ending cycle when I go back to work 😕

Say a prayer for my wife and daughter. We think they both have it now 😢

Today I got tested for Covid-19. Now I just wait for the results which can take 2-5 days. I’m an “essential employee” and if I test positive, then I got exposed while at work. So please, PLEASE STAY HOME! Don’t put the people who are having to work at risk.

@MrsP123 Depends on your symptoms. If you have a bad cough, then something like mucinex to break up the congestion in your chest. If you don’t have a bad cough, then I always take alka-seltzer cold. Zinc always helps me out too, it seems to help me kick it faster.
